Title: An Act Regarding Charges to Uninsured Patients for COVID-19
Official Title: An Act Regarding Charges to Uninsured Patients for COVID-19
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 917
H.P. 582 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
Vaccines
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 5, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Health Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered
printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MORRIS of Turner.
Cosponsored by Representatives: PAUL of Winterport, POIRIER of Skowhegan, QUINT of
Hodgdon, SWALLOW of Houlton.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §1718-G, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 28, Pt. A, §2, is amended by
3 amending the section headnote to read:
4 §1718-G. Requirements for notice to patients of costs for COVID-19 screening and
5 testing and prohibited charges for COVID-19 vaccination for uninsured
6 patients
7 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §1718-G, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 28, Pt. A, §2, is
8 repealed.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill repeals the provision of law that prohibits health care providers from charging
1111 uninsured patients for administering a COVID-19 vaccine.
Page 1 - 132LR0782(01)
